</p></div>"}

To make boulders, either use cardboard to make it flat, or a painted cotton ball to it a three-dimensional appearance. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a0/Make-a-Diorama-of-the-Civil-War-Step-4Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Diorama-of-the-Civil-War-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a0/Make-a-Diorama-of-the-Civil-War-Step-4Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Diorama-of-the-Civil-War-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":334,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":552.2527472527472,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

To add a hill, find card stock of the right size, bend the edges to be glued and press them to either the bottom of the box or the wall and glue them. Once the glue is dry, paint them an appropriate color. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/64/Make-a-Diorama-of-the-Civil-War-Step-4Bullet3.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Diorama-of-the-Civil-War-Step-4Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/64/Make-a-Diorama-of-the-Civil-War-Step-4Bullet3.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Diorama-of-the-Civil-War-Step-4Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":334,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":552.2527472527472,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
